If you want to automate wood production you need a bit of redstone magic, clickers and fertilizer. I'd recommend a selection of items like these. All you need is to supply power and keep a steady stream of items to plant, fertilize and harvest with. These 7 easy steps will teach you how to set it up!

Construction Guidelines:
1. Place dirt in middle
2. Place cobble on all 4 sides of dirt
3. Place the 2 NOT gates facing the same direction in one axis on the cobble
4. Place 2 clickers facing each other in the other axis on the cobble
5. Set one clicker to right+sneak - put saplings here, the other to right - put phytogro here.
6. In the direction the NOT gates is facing place 4 clickers on the wall facing the center. All on left click. Place a spaxelhoe in each
7. Place red alloy wire up the sides of these and connect to the NOT gate.

Congratulations! You should now have a working wood farm, thats very slow. Crank up the speed on those clickers. P.S. a good tip is for the lowest of the 4 clickers to be slower than the rest. Now for the real challenge of optimizing and automating!
